Wrote `context_harness/operator/contracts/round_navigation_r1/eval_protocol.md`.

Tension: runtime screenshot capture needs a navigation mechanism between tabs; `simctl io screenshot` captures state but does not itself select tabs, so the protocol allows XCUITest, accessibility automation, or documented coordinate taps before each `xcrun simctl io booted screenshot`.

The three files are coherent for implementation: spec defines the 5-tab model and stubs, acceptance gives grep/test/screenshot criteria, and eval protocol specifies factual capture paths and commands.
